1
00:03:30,535 --> 00:03:33,811
Read the back-page in Jagriti?
- Yes, and I'm wondering. . .

2
00:03:33,895 --> 00:03:39,253
how the news of the mines got to the
presses despite Mr Das being in place

3
00:03:39,335 --> 00:03:43,214
Got to thrash it out
at the board meeting

4
00:03:56,695 --> 00:03:58,287
Wait

5
00:04:03,735 --> 00:04:09,605
Hello, my chest is a bit of an
inconvenience for your umbrella

6
00:04:12,975 --> 00:04:16,091
Where's your friend?
- My friend? Jiten. . . ?

7
00:04:16,175 --> 00:04:21,533
Where is he?
- Returned to Calcutta yesterday

8
00:04:21,615 --> 00:04:24,652
Came directly to the office,
after I left for the day

9
00:04:24,815 --> 00:04:27,807
Since then, no news

10
00:04:28,415 --> 00:04:31,373
Umbrella ! On my foot

11
00:04:31,655 --> 00:04:34,089
Please hold it aloft?

12
00:04:43,815 --> 00:04:47,649
Send Jiten to me as soon as he
comes to office. Understand?

13
00:04:47,735 --> 00:04:50,408
Whatever you say. Bye

14
00:05:00,935 --> 00:05:02,607
Profile, first class!

15
00:05:03,095 --> 00:05:05,734
Front, super class!
- What. . . ?

16
00:05:06,255 --> 00:05:14,685
My compliments. I'm Mr Chunilal,
chief photographer. You are. . . ?

17
00:05:17,895 --> 00:05:20,534
Ruby! Pink diamond !

18
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:25,250
What an apt name!

19
00:05:25,335 --> 00:05:28,724
Pink lips, pink cheeks, pink all over

20
00:05:33,335 --> 00:05:35,530
Since when have you been here?

21
00:05:36,775 --> 00:05:40,450
Day before yesterday.
- I've been here for years

22
00:05:43,535 --> 00:05:47,210
If you have any
problems here, just tell me

23
00:05:48,935 --> 00:05:52,530
I got a link right
upto the managing director

24
00:05:53,855 --> 00:05:59,293
Right upto the managing director?
- I meet her every evening for tea

25
00:06:00,815 --> 00:06:02,089
The managing director

26
00:06:04,895 --> 00:06:07,967
This is no time for tea

27
00:06:17,255 --> 00:06:19,371
Great

28
00:06:22,455 --> 00:06:24,491
Wake up, it's morning

29
00:06:25,735 --> 00:06:29,887
The news editor has summoned you.
- Give me some time

30
00:06:29,975 --> 00:06:35,333
On the double. This morning,
he's missing you dearly

31
00:06:35,415 --> 00:06:38,612
What have you been upto?
- You'll get to know in a while

32
00:06:39,095 --> 00:06:44,294
In a while? Why, what's to happen?
- War. Between truth and falsehood

33
00:06:45,455 --> 00:06:52,724
War. . . ? No, not today, I'm in
the mood for romance. Yes dear?

34
00:06:53,575 --> 00:06:55,327
This dear is cut off for now!

35
00:06:59,815 --> 00:07:03,524
Are you the news editor?
- Yes

36
00:07:03,935 --> 00:07:10,249
Mr Das, Seth Gulabchand says that
the story on his mines is incorrect

37
00:07:10,775 --> 00:07:14,164
Absolutely incorrect, sir! I
didn't give permission to publish it

38
00:07:14,575 --> 00:07:18,647
That Jiten Gupta did it.
- Who is this Jiten Gupta?

39
00:07:18,815 --> 00:07:22,285
One of our reporters.
- It's his news

40
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:25,731
He forged my signature
and sent it to the presses

41
00:07:26,655 --> 00:07:28,611
Forgery. . . ?

42
00:07:29,815 --> 00:07:33,854
The managing director ought to
take note of the disciplinary aspect

43
00:07:35,895 --> 00:07:39,854
Mr Das, you may leave.
- Fine

44
00:07:41,255 --> 00:07:48,969
Madam, did we invest millions in your
newspaper to bring ourselves to harm?

45
00:07:49,335 --> 00:07:52,930
We ought to profit. Only profit

46
00:07:58,215 --> 00:08:02,094
Is this a request or a threat?

47
00:08:02,575 --> 00:08:04,212
Not to misunderstand

48
00:08:04,815 --> 00:08:06,248
A request

49
00:08:06,495 --> 00:08:10,534
From this newspaper, our
businesses ought to gain. Not lose

50
00:08:11,215 --> 00:08:15,447
Your involvement with the newspaper
is only in the share of profits

51
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:22,211
Deciding the policy of the newspaper,
running it, is my responsibility

52
00:08:23,255 --> 00:08:25,928
And I am fully aware
of my responsibilities

53
00:08:53,135 --> 00:08:55,603
Got to take a look at
the book before sundown

54
00:09:09,095 --> 00:09:12,974
Drinking in office?
- The office being the problem. . .

55
00:09:13,055 --> 00:09:15,649
here's right where I take care of it.
- I'll do it for you

56
00:09:15,735 --> 00:09:20,251
What are you doing? ! You've
spilled half! Let me have the rest

57
00:09:20,335 --> 00:09:25,455
No, I'm throwing it all away.
- Go on ! I've got money

58
00:09:25,735 --> 00:09:27,771
That was a quarter of a bottle.
I'll buy myself a whole bottle

59
00:09:27,855 --> 00:09:29,891
Let's see how you do that.
- Mr Gupta. . .

60
00:09:30,175 --> 00:09:32,405
What is it?
- Madam wants to see Mr Gupta

61
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:39,045
Calling you ! For the first time!
You're surely getting a promotion

62
00:09:39,975 --> 00:09:43,092
Give my money back!
- You aren't getting it back

63
00:09:43,295 --> 00:09:49,006
You think I can't buy on credit?
At month's end, I drink on credit

64
00:10:06,015 --> 00:10:08,973
Are you Jiten Gupta?
- Yes

65
00:10:10,575 --> 00:10:14,250
The news about the mines is yours?
- Yes

66
00:10:15,495 --> 00:10:19,329
Without permission of
the news editor? - Yes

67
00:10:36,975 --> 00:10:43,448
Your job is getting the news.
Publishing is the news editor's job

68
00:10:43,775 --> 00:10:47,050
I know, but. . .
- Why are you indiscipline?

69
00:10:47,695 --> 00:10:50,163
For the sake of the
ideals of this newspaper

70
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:54,006
Isn't this our motto?
''Let the Truth prevail''

71
00:10:55,295 --> 00:10:59,003
My news is correct. The mines
are in a precarious condition

72
00:10:59,215 --> 00:11:04,335
They might collapse at any time.
Several miners might be killed

73
00:11:08,695 --> 00:11:14,691
You shall state your case without
getting carried away. Talk business

74
00:11:14,975 --> 00:11:18,729
I'm not getting carried away.
Tell me, what is more precious?

75
00:11:18,815 --> 00:11:21,932
The lives of the miners?
Or office discipline?

76
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:27,969
I wish you saw for yourself
the poor miners deep underground

77
00:11:28,295 --> 00:11:32,413
Sans fresh air and the
heat could melt your brains

78
00:11:33,015 --> 00:11:35,529
The work conditions are stifling

79
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:41,692
You know why? If they don't
work their children will starve

80
00:11:41,775 --> 00:11:45,084
Hapless as they are, they
mustn't be oppressed in this manner

81
00:11:45,895 --> 00:11:49,092
What oppression?
- I have the evidence

82
00:11:49,575 --> 00:11:52,647
The mine-owners are playing with their
lives. Just look at my photographs

83
00:11:53,175 --> 00:11:58,248
Just look at the state. Ceilings,
about to cave in, flooding waters

84
00:12:00,135 --> 00:12:02,045
Do take a look, madam

85
00:12:03,615 --> 00:12:06,971
Why didn't you show
this to the news editor?

86
00:12:07,135 --> 00:12:12,812
I did, but he refused to
publish it. I hear he's their man

87
00:12:13,975 --> 00:12:16,808
Whose man?
- The mine owners'

88
00:12:16,935 --> 00:12:18,084
Enough !

89
00:12:19,135 --> 00:12:24,653
Mr Das has been working with us for
eight years. Not a word against him

90
00:12:25,655 --> 00:12:29,091
As you please. One last thing

91
00:12:29,175 --> 00:12:33,851
I have no more time.
- The working of those mines must stop

92
00:12:33,935 --> 00:12:37,449
You may leave.
- It's a matter of lives

93
00:12:37,535 --> 00:12:39,685
Stop arguing.
- Give me a hearing

94
00:12:39,775 --> 00:12:42,733
I told you. You may leave.
I wish to hear no more

95
00:12:43,015 --> 00:12:46,723
Why won't you? You must.
You can, if you wish. . .

96
00:12:46,815 --> 00:12:52,970
use the newspaper to save lives.
Else, today or tomorrow. . .

97
00:12:53,055 --> 00:12:56,364
the mines will cave in,
crushing miners to death

98
00:12:56,615 --> 00:12:59,527
Women will be widowed,
children will be orphaned

99
00:12:59,775 --> 00:13:02,369
And you will be responsible

100
00:13:02,455 --> 00:13:04,013
Silence

101
00:13:12,335 --> 00:13:16,931
I hear this paper fought for
the people, for the truth. . .

102
00:13:17,015 --> 00:13:22,567
in you father's times.
The daughter, I see. . .

103
00:13:23,015 --> 00:13:25,324
has sold out to the capitalists

104
00:13:27,255 --> 00:13:33,774
This insolence has cost you your job.
- Not my life, I hope

105
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:38,291
As long as I preserve my courage,
employers, there will be many

106
00:13:40,535 --> 00:13:46,644
Maybe you never heard the
saying about the Eternal Spring

107
00:13:47,015 --> 00:13:50,769
The arrival of The
Spring will never cease

108
00:14:32,415 --> 00:14:35,372
Who else is around?
- I'm laughing it out all alone

109
00:14:35,815 --> 00:14:39,444
Just read a lovely joke

110
00:14:47,135 --> 00:14:48,409
I failed?

111
00:14:49,975 --> 00:14:51,328
Complete failure

112
00:14:52,535 --> 00:14:55,447
But the results are expected tomorrow.
How come you've found out today?

113
00:14:57,615 --> 00:15:00,493
A friend told me.
- Your friend is talking rot

114
00:15:02,415 --> 00:15:07,204
He works at the university.
- At the university?

115
00:15:08,255 --> 00:15:09,734
Then. . .

116
00:15:14,535 --> 00:15:17,174
What happened, Baby?
- The telephone

117
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:19,809
And. . .
- Conversation

118
00:15:19,895 --> 00:15:22,125
And. . . ?
- Don't you see? I'm in tears!

119
00:15:22,215 --> 00:15:26,572
And why are you in tears?
- Tomorrow, Didi will scream at me

120
00:15:26,655 --> 00:15:30,568
What for? I've never
heard her screaming at you

121
00:15:30,655 --> 00:15:36,332
That's why I'm so sacred !
No! I can't show her my face

122
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:38,646
Not anymore

123
00:16:03,895 --> 00:16:08,889
Would it cost you your
tongue to apologise?

124
00:16:09,295 --> 00:16:10,694
Yes

125
00:16:11,655 --> 00:16:13,725
Hear that, brother?

126
00:16:13,815 --> 00:16:18,570
Take a good look at him. The
one and only, in all of India

127
00:16:19,095 --> 00:16:21,563
As much fun as an ass has in summer. . .

128
00:16:21,655 --> 00:16:24,613
this man enjoys going broke

129
00:16:24,695 --> 00:16:28,404
Sure.
- What do you mean? He just got fired

130
00:16:28,495 --> 00:16:31,089
And look at him enjoying himself

131
00:16:32,295 --> 00:16:39,564
Wonderful ! Just look at the
display of sheer nonchalance

132
00:16:41,095 --> 00:16:44,531
Come off it! I'm talking to you.
- Yes, go on

133
00:16:44,615 --> 00:16:47,925
Why didn't you apologise to her?
- Why should I?

134
00:16:48,015 --> 00:16:56,968
Indeed ! Your father left you a legacy!
So you kick the job! Not your ego

135
00:16:57,055 --> 00:17:02,003
Not ego. Ideals.
- Ideals! Indeed !

136
00:17:02,775 --> 00:17:07,848
I'm talking to you.
Just look at him, brother

137
00:17:07,935 --> 00:17:12,963
The world is making money.
And he's after ideals!

138
00:17:13,055 --> 00:17:18,288
And why not? Money isn't as
exciting as the ideal, is it?

139
00:17:20,335 --> 00:17:22,290
Move over

140
00:17:26,494 --> 00:17:32,967
Listen, your ideals won't work,
not in 1 96 2. Not listening, are you?

141
00:17:33,295 --> 00:17:37,607
You'll die starving, soon.
Let's see who gives you a job

142
00:17:37,935 --> 00:17:40,210
Lots Chuni Lal, lots

143
00:17:51,095 --> 00:17:54,974
''Let the gardener be gone''

144
00:17:55,415 --> 00:17:59,090
''But in Eden it always blossoms''

145
00:17:59,455 --> 00:18:03,687
''The Spring always returns''

146
00:18:03,775 --> 00:18:07,734
''Spring will always return''

147
00:18:53,415 --> 00:18:57,533
''Don't let yourself tire,
don't let yourself be stifled''

148
00:18:57,775 --> 00:19:01,768
''Go on, singing your tune''

149
00:19:10,295 --> 00:19:14,652
''Among thorns, make
flowers blossom. . . ''

150
00:19:14,735 --> 00:19:18,694
''use them to fill your emptiness''

151
00:19:27,095 --> 00:19:31,327
''Let the wind fan the flames''

152
00:19:31,415 --> 00:19:35,488
''Let there be venom in the air''

153
00:19:35,575 --> 00:19:39,807
''Yet The Spring always returns''

154
00:19:39,895 --> 00:19:43,968
''Spring will always return''

155
00:19:44,055 --> 00:19:48,173
''Let the gardener be gone''

156
00:19:48,255 --> 00:19:52,533
''But in Eden it always blossoms''

157
00:20:05,215 --> 00:20:09,049
''What is light, what is darkness?''

158
00:20:09,455 --> 00:20:13,368
''I belong to none''

159
00:20:22,135 --> 00:20:30,327
''Your dreams, your desires,
are all you have''

160
00:20:39,015 --> 00:20:43,452
''Let the world treat you mercilessly''

161
00:20:43,535 --> 00:20:47,528
''Let not the climes suit you''

162
00:20:47,615 --> 00:20:51,767
''Yet, The Spring always returns''

163
00:20:51,855 --> 00:20:56,133
''Spring will always return''

164
00:20:56,215 --> 00:21:00,413
''Let the gardener be gone''

165
00:21:00,495 --> 00:21:04,647
''But in Eden it always blossoms''

166
00:21:58,175 --> 00:22:00,166
What are you upto?

167
00:22:02,735 --> 00:22:06,774
Oh how cruel a world this is! - How
cruelly has your world dealt you?

168
00:22:06,855 --> 00:22:12,248
I can't even jump when I want to die!
- Why do you wish to die?

169
00:22:12,535 --> 00:22:17,131
How are you concerned? Intruding
upon someone's privacy is uncivilised

170
00:22:18,415 --> 00:22:22,966
Forgive me this error.
Go on, jump. Go ahead

171
00:22:23,575 --> 00:22:26,647
It's going to take another
three quarters of an hour

172
00:22:27,335 --> 00:22:31,692
In the wait for an auspicious moment?

173
00:22:32,775 --> 00:22:35,335
Worked on it for 4 5 minutes. . .

174
00:22:35,535 --> 00:22:39,767
to get into the mood for the plunge.
In the nick of time, you transpire!

175
00:22:39,855 --> 00:22:41,766
Ruined all my efforts!

176
00:22:43,975 --> 00:22:46,773
Then I have committed a grave crime!

177
00:22:49,855 --> 00:22:53,814
Get out of this madness. Go home.
- I'm not returning

178
00:22:57,135 --> 00:22:59,251
Why is the train stopping here?

179
00:23:28,655 --> 00:23:30,964
Listen. . .

180
00:23:37,975 --> 00:23:40,330
Sprain?
- All because of you

181
00:23:40,415 --> 00:23:43,293
Had you not meddled, I wouldn't
have had to make this getaway

182
00:23:44,215 --> 00:23:49,129
Or I would've been dead by now.
- Sorry for spoiling the fun

183
00:23:49,375 --> 00:23:53,084
Let me drop you home.
- I'm not going home

184
00:23:53,855 --> 00:23:59,213
Then I shall, perforce.
- My foot hurts! Brute!

185
00:23:59,815 --> 00:24:04,127
If you must do it like
a gentleman. Pick me up

186
00:24:07,215 --> 00:24:12,050
Don't you watch films? Are
girls picked up like this?

187
00:24:12,135 --> 00:24:16,208
Yes, this is the way
every burden is carried

188
00:24:46,935 --> 00:24:50,928
Is Babli asleep?
- She locked herself in all evening

189
00:24:51,375 --> 00:24:54,014
Is she all right?
- Yes, you want me to wake her up?

190
00:24:54,095 --> 00:24:55,608
No, let her sleep

191
00:25:00,815 --> 00:25:04,046
You won't give me your name
and address? - No, no and no!

192
00:25:04,135 --> 00:25:06,603
Let's see, for how long.
- Till eternity

193
00:25:06,695 --> 00:25:09,368
Until then I am pursuing you

194
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:14,494
Look. . .

195
00:25:17,455 --> 00:25:20,128
All you need is the reins

196
00:25:22,015 --> 00:25:23,846
Step down.
- I won't

197
00:25:24,535 --> 00:25:28,130
You aren't on mule-back.
It's my back. Get off

198
00:25:28,215 --> 00:25:29,533
Get off, I say

199
00:25:35,375 --> 00:25:39,687
This man brought me here forcibly!
- I'm taking her home

200
00:25:39,855 --> 00:25:43,370
I won't, won't and I won't!

201
00:25:43,455 --> 00:25:47,733
Why are you limping?
- He gave me the limp

202
00:25:47,815 --> 00:25:51,808
Your woman she won't go home with you.
So you beat her up? Aren't you ashamed?

203
00:25:53,695 --> 00:25:59,213
Why not? If women won't stay at home,
will men not raise their hands?

204
00:25:59,735 --> 00:26:03,409
If men raise their hands,
will women stay at home?

205
00:26:04,695 --> 00:26:08,573
You're right. Please save me.
From him. - Don't you worry, sister

206
00:26:08,655 --> 00:26:12,773
He won't even point
a finger at you. Come inside

207
00:26:13,575 --> 00:26:15,884
You will keep watching !

208
00:26:16,775 --> 00:26:21,929
God save us from these women.
Be nice to them. . .

209
00:26:22,015 --> 00:26:26,884
and they want to perch on your head.
- In my case, it has been the back

210
00:26:27,375 --> 00:26:30,173
Who knows what is in store!

211
00:26:39,455 --> 00:26:44,051
I see. Tit for tat, eh? He
vanishes even without waking me up

212
00:26:48,535 --> 00:26:51,686
When is the next train back?
- Tomorrow

213
00:26:51,775 --> 00:26:58,089
Stood me up for a whole night.
Scoundrel ! I won't spare him

214
00:27:09,575 --> 00:27:11,805
This fellow won't get up so easily

215
00:27:14,935 --> 00:27:17,369
Can I find anything here?

216
00:27:17,455 --> 00:27:21,289
Ticket, ticket!
- I got a pass. You got any problems?

217
00:27:21,375 --> 00:27:25,050
Show me your pass.
- Hold this

218
00:27:30,895 --> 00:27:33,329
Son of a gun !
- What did you say?

219
00:27:33,975 --> 00:27:37,331
Not you brother, not you.
- You just said it

220
00:27:37,415 --> 00:27:41,293
I was describing someone else.
But if that describes you. . .

221
00:27:41,375 --> 00:27:46,005
well, you're a son of a gun !
- Hold your tongue, I say!

222
00:27:46,095 --> 00:27:52,045
Pipe down ! You're talking to a
press photographer, do you know?

223
00:27:52,135 --> 00:27:56,367
Irrespective, the fine is 2. 50.
- Pipe down, I said

224
00:27:56,455 --> 00:28:01,973
I'll pay you double. Plus a tip.
But not today, tomorrow

225
00:28:03,135 --> 00:28:05,524
You want to bribe me? Constable!

226
00:28:05,615 --> 00:28:10,166
The constable takes a cut?

227
00:28:10,255 --> 00:28:15,249
Why not call in the
station master too?

228
00:28:15,335 --> 00:28:19,772
The three of you can freak out!
- No!

229
00:28:34,535 --> 00:28:38,528
Hurts less. . . ?
- Vanished

230
00:28:40,055 --> 00:28:43,525
What a way to treat you.
He must be cruel

231
00:28:44,495 --> 00:28:46,213
Very cruel

232
00:28:46,655 --> 00:28:50,533
Any children?
- Ask him

233
00:28:51,215 --> 00:28:55,845
Him. . . ? Why not you?
- How would I know how many he has?

234
00:28:56,495 --> 00:29:00,373
Goodness! Is he wayward?

235
00:29:01,695 --> 00:29:04,254
Outrageous.
- Is that so?

236
00:29:04,335 --> 00:29:07,008
Then he'll mend his
ways before he leaves

237
00:29:11,455 --> 00:29:13,843
Are you human? Or a demon?

238
00:29:14,335 --> 00:29:17,611
You have a woman at home.
Yet you are wayward?

239
00:29:17,775 --> 00:29:20,608
What rot are you saying?
- Shut up!

240
00:29:20,695 --> 00:29:25,166
Poor thing has such bad luck to be
tied to him! I ask her, how many kids?

241
00:29:25,255 --> 00:29:29,612
She says, ask my husband. Such a
demon ! Always running after girls

242
00:29:29,695 --> 00:29:33,004
She's lying ! I've got
nothing to do with her

243
00:29:33,095 --> 00:29:38,089
Then why were you backpacking her?
You think you can fool me? Move

244
00:29:38,895 --> 00:29:42,012
What are you doing?
- You stay back

245
00:29:42,095 --> 00:29:44,563
You'll mend your ways before you leave

246
00:29:44,655 --> 00:29:48,204
In you go. Apologise to your woman.
- But she isn't. . .

247
00:29:48,295 --> 00:29:51,173
She has suffered enough.
Apologise to her

248
00:29:51,735 --> 00:29:55,444
Go inside Bolt the door

249
00:30:00,735 --> 00:30:04,694
Why did you shut the door?
- I'm being forced. . .

250
00:30:06,695 --> 00:30:11,928
to spend the night here.
- Here? With me?

251
00:30:14,695 --> 00:30:17,971
Why did you tell her
we're man and woman?

252
00:30:18,695 --> 00:30:22,448
Is that a lie? A man is one who
grows a beard. The rest are women

253
00:30:23,735 --> 00:30:28,889
Brilliant! In local parlance,
man-woman means man and wife

254
00:31:39,895 --> 00:31:41,328
Once more

255
00:31:43,135 --> 00:31:44,454
Get lost

256
00:31:52,135 --> 00:31:57,528
You're such a savage! You ought
to take a lesson from this couple

257
00:31:58,015 --> 00:32:01,451
No sooner than her man
woos her, she's willing

258
00:32:01,935 --> 00:32:04,448
They love each other so much

259
00:32:09,135 --> 00:32:12,366
Are you begging of your wife now?
Weren't you so brash a while ago?

260
00:32:50,615 --> 00:32:54,528
Fresh news! Newspaper

261
00:33:09,655 --> 00:33:12,931
Money
- Money. . . ? Keep it

262
00:33:29,135 --> 00:33:32,650
Address. . . Siakhala

263
00:33:33,575 --> 00:33:37,614
Name. . . Chuni Lal

264
00:34:15,534 --> 00:34:17,172
Where's Babli?
- Still asleep

265
00:34:17,255 --> 00:34:20,565
Hasn't come out of her room yet.
- What a silly girl

266
00:34:31,614 --> 00:34:34,208
This is sleeping a bit too long

267
00:34:34,574 --> 00:34:37,168
Is she all right?

268
00:34:41,175 --> 00:34:43,006
Coming, Didi ( Didi = sister)

269
00:34:46,014 --> 00:34:47,846
Hello.
- Hello

270
00:34:47,935 --> 00:34:51,529
Hi Didi ! Where's Bubbles?

271
00:34:51,614 --> 00:34:54,254
She has passed. In second division

272
00:34:54,735 --> 00:34:57,329
But where is she?
- Inside. Should be coming out

273
00:35:02,615 --> 00:35:06,607
Yesterday, I made
such a fool of Bubbles!

274
00:35:07,935 --> 00:35:09,129
Really?

275
00:35:10,415 --> 00:35:15,091
Were you saying something, Mr Verma?
- Yes, as I was saying. . .

276
00:35:16,295 --> 00:35:19,173
now that Babli has passed. . .

277
00:35:21,655 --> 00:35:23,532
makes it twice as happy a day

278
00:35:25,655 --> 00:35:27,885
Bubbles isn't out yet!
Why don't you call her out?

279
00:35:55,015 --> 00:35:58,690
Sushma ! You tell your
uncle to give me my wallet

280
00:35:58,895 --> 00:36:01,887
Ma. . . uncles Jitu and
Chuni are at it again

281
00:36:01,975 --> 00:36:03,124
Take that

282
00:36:03,215 --> 00:36:08,528
Fighting again, Chuni?
- For the last time

283
00:36:09,855 --> 00:36:14,246
Not a chance of another quarrel !
Never again will I see his face!

284
00:36:14,335 --> 00:36:17,168
Never again will I talk to him!
- Don't worry, Didi

285
00:36:17,375 --> 00:36:21,926
In 5 minutes, he'll start talking.
- Not in 5 lifetimes!

286
00:36:23,255 --> 00:36:27,533
Didi, you tell him not to talk
to me. Our friendship is over

287
00:36:27,815 --> 00:36:30,045
But what happened?
- What not?

288
00:36:30,135 --> 00:36:32,649
He deserted me on the train,
while I was asleep

289
00:36:32,735 --> 00:36:36,444
Curse you ! You'll never land a job!

290
00:36:36,535 --> 00:36:38,412
All night, I was
locked away in the lock-up

291
00:36:38,495 --> 00:36:44,650
This morning I pawned my camera to pay
the fine! He'd rather I was in jail !

292
00:36:50,415 --> 00:36:54,203
* * *Now I know why you said
I'd talk to him in 5 minutes

293
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:57,810
You wanted to swallow
my money! Cough it up!

294
00:36:57,895 --> 00:37:00,853
I didn't even open your wallet,
Johny. I swear it on you

295
00:37:00,935 --> 00:37:03,813
Why swear on me. . . ? Find someone else!

296
00:37:03,895 --> 00:37:08,685
Nine bucks yesterday and eight today.
Where did the ninth one go?

297
00:37:10,975 --> 00:37:13,694
Could she have. . . ?

298
00:37:14,215 --> 00:37:16,570
Out with it. Fast. I got to go to work

299
00:37:16,655 --> 00:37:22,173
Didi, unlike him, I haven't been
fired. - What did you say, Chuni. . . ?

300
00:37:23,455 --> 00:37:25,764
It's true

301
00:37:28,095 --> 00:37:31,404
You want me to lie to Didi?

302
00:37:38,255 --> 00:37:41,452
Stop blabbering. Here's money

303
00:37:44,055 --> 00:37:50,528
Have you really lost your job?
- So what? He hasn't compromised. . .

304
00:37:50,615 --> 00:37:53,924
on his ideals! Now he and his
ideals are going to sit at home

305
00:37:54,015 --> 00:37:58,611
And so what if he gets nothing
to eat? He can live off his ideals

306
00:38:00,175 --> 00:38:03,485
When will you come to your senses?
Inflation is soaring

307
00:38:03,575 --> 00:38:08,330
How will we make ends meet?
- As long as I'm capable. . .

308
00:38:08,575 --> 00:38:10,645
we won't starve

309
00:38:44,575 --> 00:38:49,285
135 workers killed in mine collapse

310
00:38:52,175 --> 00:38:56,088
You can, if you wish, use
the newspaper to save lives

311
00:38:56,535 --> 00:39:00,732
Else, today or tomorrow, the mines
will cave in, crushing miners to death

312
00:39:00,815 --> 00:39:05,889
Women will be widowed,
children will be orphaned

313
00:39:05,975 --> 00:39:09,411
And you will be responsible

314
00:39:17,535 --> 00:39:21,163
I hear this paper fought for
the people, for the truth. . .

315
00:39:21,255 --> 00:39:24,372
in you father's times

316
00:39:25,335 --> 00:39:28,213
The daughter, I see. . .

317
00:39:28,295 --> 00:39:31,287
has sold out to the capitalists

318
00:39:34,695 --> 00:39:36,128
Are you all right?

319
00:39:38,655 --> 00:39:45,367
In my father's times, this newspaper
fought for the truth. Always

320
00:39:45,455 --> 00:39:50,006
I came to tell you exactly that.
135 miners killed

321
00:39:50,095 --> 00:39:54,850
It's in all the papers. Except ours

322
00:39:57,015 --> 00:39:59,404
Let the Truth prevail

323
00:40:02,175 --> 00:40:08,410
My father's legacy.
Reduced to mere sham? Perhaps

324
00:40:13,255 --> 00:40:17,851
Going looking for a job. Bless me.
- May God give you success

325
00:40:36,975 --> 00:40:38,089
Come on

326
00:40:38,175 --> 00:40:42,009
Uncle Chuni ! In a grand car?
- Whose car is it?

327
00:40:42,815 --> 00:40:47,764
Riding in the backseat! Door held
open by the chauffeur! Didn't you see?

328
00:40:47,855 --> 00:40:49,334
Come on.
- Where to. . . ?

329
00:40:49,415 --> 00:40:51,975
Let me give you a ride
on the backseat! Come on !

330
00:41:29,495 --> 00:41:32,692
Oh you. . . ? One minute

331
00:41:32,775 --> 00:41:36,370
It's full of dust. I haven't
been in here in a long time

332
00:41:38,495 --> 00:41:42,283
A vast business is
sometimes an aberration too

333
00:41:44,415 --> 00:41:46,804
How did I ever forget this place?

334
00:41:48,335 --> 00:41:55,207
Looks like an ancient press office.
- Yes. Daddy's. Years ago. . .

335
00:41:55,295 --> 00:41:57,092
this is where he started out from,
publishing the paper

336
00:41:57,175 --> 00:41:59,848
Really?
- This used to be Daddy's table

337
00:42:00,735 --> 00:42:05,365
I've left everything as it was.
I do the cleaning and dusting myself

338
00:42:05,455 --> 00:42:09,732
I don't let anyone else in here.
- Forgive me, I didn't know that

339
00:42:09,935 --> 00:42:14,486
I'll wait for you in your office.
- No, for you, no bars

340
00:42:14,935 --> 00:42:18,974
Don't leave
- Why have you called me?

341
00:42:22,215 --> 00:42:26,572
After the other day, I wonder
what you might be thinking of me

342
00:42:29,055 --> 00:42:32,933
I'm sure it's nothing nice.
- I have no complaints against you

343
00:42:35,015 --> 00:42:36,812
Really?
- Yes

344
00:42:43,295 --> 00:42:50,406
You know, there was never
anyone who dared to talk me down

345
00:42:52,215 --> 00:42:55,093
For the first time,
the other day, it was you

346
00:42:57,135 --> 00:42:59,808
When I think of it, you were right

347
00:43:02,575 --> 00:43:05,372
You haven't told me
why you have called me

348
00:43:05,735 --> 00:43:12,925
I. . . this newspaper needs you.
- I too need a job

349
00:43:13,375 --> 00:43:17,527
But working with your news
editor might be difficult

350
00:43:19,175 --> 00:43:25,523
Mr Das has been taken off the job. In
his stead, the news editor will be. . .

351
00:43:26,055 --> 00:43:30,094
you.
- I. . . ? News editor?

352
00:43:30,175 --> 00:43:38,446
Yes, you. With you, my father's ideal
will flourish again. I am confident

353
00:43:38,535 --> 00:43:40,207
Thank you

354
00:43:41,735 --> 00:43:44,203
That was the ideal I was born into

355
00:43:47,215 --> 00:43:50,173
I feel so calm when I come here

356
00:43:51,095 --> 00:43:56,089
I relive my childhood

357
00:43:57,055 --> 00:44:03,812
As if Daddy is still here. For hours
I talk to myself, I talk to him

358
00:44:05,015 --> 00:44:07,051
Talking to yourself?

359
00:44:08,695 --> 00:44:12,290
Don't you tell anyone.
People will think I'm mad.

360
00:44:13,175 --> 00:44:15,609
Maybe you like solitude

361
00:44:17,295 --> 00:44:25,088
Solitude? Who ever likes that?
But slowly, it becomes a habit

362
00:44:27,415 --> 00:44:30,087
The sun comes in here
quite late in the day

363
00:44:30,775 --> 00:44:33,608
Better late than never

364
00:44:38,015 --> 00:44:41,973
Mr Chuni Lal. . . hereabouts?
- Yes, come in

365
00:44:47,335 --> 00:44:50,566
He lives here?
- No, over there

366
00:44:51,335 --> 00:44:57,365
But he has his meals with us.
Ma, someone's here for Uncle Chuni

367
00:44:58,015 --> 00:45:02,087
You're his niece?
- Not his own

368
00:45:03,215 --> 00:45:08,243
Uncle Chuni is my uncle's friend.
This is my mother

369
00:45:08,335 --> 00:45:09,609
Greetings

370
00:45:10,735 --> 00:45:13,886
Greetings. Sit

371
00:45:14,535 --> 00:45:18,129
Sushma, take this inside

372
00:45:19,375 --> 00:45:21,809
Please sit.
- Be seated

373
00:45:31,135 --> 00:45:34,810
Are you from town?
- Yes. I wandered a bit

374
00:45:34,895 --> 00:45:38,251
But I'm steadfast in my resolve.
I had decided not to return. . .

375
00:45:38,335 --> 00:45:42,294
until I found Chuni Lal's address.
- Chuni is away in Calcutta on work

376
00:45:43,015 --> 00:45:48,533
Won't be back before ten tonight.
- Ten tonight? Blast

377
00:45:49,455 --> 00:45:51,969
Waiting that long. . .

378
00:45:52,055 --> 00:45:55,013
I'm a girl you see. Had I been a boy,
it'd be different

379
00:45:58,295 --> 00:46:00,331
What's your name?

380
00:46:00,415 --> 00:46:03,805
Please be informal
with me. You are my elder

381
00:46:04,495 --> 00:46:07,851
May I address you as my sister?
- Sure

382
00:46:08,015 --> 00:46:12,964
Look at me Didi, I'm all grown up.
And they still call me by my pet name

383
00:46:13,055 --> 00:46:16,569
No one uses my real name!
Sunita. Isn't that a nice name?

384
00:46:16,655 --> 00:46:18,725
Lovely name.
- My name's Sushma

385
00:46:18,815 --> 00:46:23,650
Sushma's a lovely name too.
But Chuni Lal. . .

386
00:46:27,575 --> 00:46:29,452
You even have a guava tree?

387
00:46:29,535 --> 00:46:33,767
Lovely house, Didi ! Sushma, you
must be eating raw guavas everyday!

388
00:46:34,015 --> 00:46:36,609
We only get the ripe ones.
The ones in the marketplace

389
00:46:36,695 --> 00:46:41,564
Would you like to eat guavas?
Let me get you some fresh ones

390
00:46:43,975 --> 00:46:49,208
Everything's nice about
Uncle Chuni. Except one thing

391
00:46:49,375 --> 00:46:55,610
He bosses over girls.
- No. He drinks

392
00:46:57,335 --> 00:47:00,566
Booze. . . ?
- You didn't know?

393
00:47:01,655 --> 00:47:07,093
Don't you say I told you !
He'll twist my ears!

394
00:47:16,095 --> 00:47:18,131
Didi !
- What happened?

395
00:47:18,415 --> 00:47:21,930
Come here! Open your mouth !

396
00:47:22,015 --> 00:47:24,654
What's this?
- Open your mouth

397
00:47:25,375 --> 00:47:27,935
Sushma ! For you too! Take this

398
00:47:28,735 --> 00:47:30,168
Gone!

399
00:47:30,735 --> 00:47:33,374
Still got the sweets. Take it

400
00:47:34,895 --> 00:47:38,331
What are we celebrating?
Are you getting married?

401
00:47:40,975 --> 00:47:45,093
Can any girl ever like him?
Look at this face. Vegetable

402
00:47:45,175 --> 00:47:49,453
I'm a non-vegetarian, you snake

403
00:47:49,935 --> 00:47:56,534
Your brother is such a snake!
I buy sweets to celebrate his job

404
00:47:56,615 --> 00:48:00,129
Still he bites!
- Has he found a job?

405
00:48:00,215 --> 00:48:06,768
He can't even beg for a living !
My recommendation worked

406
00:48:08,255 --> 00:48:11,008
Ms Sunita was here.
- Who. . . ?

407
00:48:11,455 --> 00:48:14,252
Sunita ! What's that?

408
00:48:14,335 --> 00:48:17,293
Stop joking. I liked her

409
00:48:17,375 --> 00:48:20,447
Came looking for you this afternoon.
- A girl. . . ?

410
00:48:20,535 --> 00:48:22,491
She left this letter for you

411
00:48:37,855 --> 00:48:40,813
Not light enough to read

412
00:48:41,335 --> 00:48:45,294
Didi, serve us dinner. I'll be back

413
00:48:57,655 --> 00:48:59,725
Vegetable

414
00:49:02,295 --> 00:49:08,211
Burn in jealousy. I got the letter

415
00:49:17,095 --> 00:49:19,086
That's a fitting reply.

416
00:49:19,175 --> 00:49:23,965
You'll be even more
jealous if you were to hear

417
00:49:25,695 --> 00:49:30,166
She writes,
''You must be wondering. . . ''

418
00:49:30,495 --> 00:49:37,765
''how I found your address''

419
00:49:37,975 --> 00:49:42,810
''7 : 30 pm tomorrow''

420
00:49:43,135 --> 00:49:49,290
''At Brijwasi Sweets on Chowringhee''

421
00:49:49,375 --> 00:49:52,048
''Make sure. . . ''

422
00:49:52,135 --> 00:49:54,251
Sure

423
00:49:55,935 --> 00:49:58,051
''Make sure you see me''

424
00:49:58,295 --> 00:50:04,484
''You may not know me by name''

425
00:50:04,695 --> 00:50:11,043
''I'm the one who had
a sprained ankle''

426
00:50:11,575 --> 00:50:13,292
One with a sprained ankle?

427
00:50:17,215 --> 00:50:21,652
Keep your hands to yourself.
It's a lady's letter

428
00:50:26,015 --> 00:50:28,404
You see. . .

429
00:50:28,615 --> 00:50:33,973
she's as dainty as an angel,
as delicate as a blossom

430
00:50:34,055 --> 00:50:37,411
The day before yesterday,
when I held her hand. . .

431
00:50:37,655 --> 00:50:40,123
her wrist seemed to elude me.
- Congratulations

432
00:50:41,255 --> 00:50:45,248
So you're going to see her
at 7 : 30 tomorrow evening?

433
00:51:34,415 --> 00:51:35,609
Oh, hello

434
00:51:37,295 --> 00:51:39,650
Forgive me, I was engrossed

435
00:51:40,815 --> 00:51:42,612
Lovely novel

436
00:51:44,135 --> 00:51:46,603
Get on with it.
- Now. . . ?

437
00:51:47,135 --> 00:51:49,251
I'll keep it for later

438
00:51:56,455 --> 00:51:58,525
After you

439
00:52:03,735 --> 00:52:05,532
My name is Amita

440
00:52:05,615 --> 00:52:09,654
You can call me Ms Amita,
instead of Madam

441
00:52:12,055 --> 00:52:15,013
Not on every occasion would
I like you to defer to me. . .

442
00:52:15,095 --> 00:52:20,328
for being the managing director.
- Not out of awe. I do regard you

443
00:52:22,935 --> 00:52:25,529
I see. . . ?
- Yes. I respect you a lot

444
00:52:26,615 --> 00:52:30,243
Any particular reason?

445
00:52:30,615 --> 00:52:33,209
I think you're good at heart. . .

446
00:52:33,295 --> 00:52:36,890
a beautiful person

447
00:52:38,455 --> 00:52:41,811
Beautiful. . .
- What's on your mind?

448
00:52:44,375 --> 00:52:50,450
You fancy grams?
- Sometimes I miss breakfast

449
00:52:52,015 --> 00:52:55,723
Grams for breakfast?
- I just make do

450
00:52:55,815 --> 00:52:58,375
Very crisp. Would you like some?

451
00:53:00,135 --> 00:53:02,968
I think the phone's
ringing in my office

452
00:53:10,255 --> 00:53:15,773
All dressed up and going to meet whom?
- No one. Just trying out the fit

453
00:53:15,855 --> 00:53:18,164
Then come to the club with me.
- With you?

454
00:53:18,255 --> 00:53:21,565
You must.
- Of course I will. . . but. . .

455
00:53:22,295 --> 00:53:25,970
there's a murder case
I must take some photos

456
00:53:26,895 --> 00:53:31,207
What if you're late?
- Just photographing a corpse

457
00:53:31,295 --> 00:53:34,128
Readymade pose!
No posturing before the camera

458
00:53:34,215 --> 00:53:38,572
Pull away the sheet and shoot.
Five minutes' job

459
00:53:38,855 --> 00:53:40,652
Let me come along too.

460
00:53:42,135 --> 00:53:46,686
No killing looks. This is pure murder

461
00:53:46,775 --> 00:53:51,212
No place for a lady to be.
- You just said it's a 5-minute job

462
00:53:51,295 --> 00:53:58,246
I'll wait outside in the cab.
- First let me find out the address

463
00:53:58,775 --> 00:54:01,369
Wait here. I'll be back

464
00:54:10,615 --> 00:54:12,366
You asked for me?

465
00:54:13,895 --> 00:54:15,726
Yes

466
00:54:15,935 --> 00:54:18,005
Yesterday I read your article
about the northeast situation

467
00:54:18,095 --> 00:54:21,723
You've been rather harsh.
Are you forgetting?

468
00:54:21,815 --> 00:54:25,728
Government policy is
brotherhood with China

469
00:54:25,815 --> 00:54:29,410
But our brethren carry knives.
Before 1 96 2 is over. . .

470
00:54:29,495 --> 00:54:33,124
they will surely do something.
- I see. . . ?

471
00:54:33,975 --> 00:54:40,813
You didn't like my article, madam?
- Not madam. Amita

472
00:54:40,895 --> 00:54:45,730
Tell me Ms Amita. My article. . .
- I like it

473
00:54:45,815 --> 00:54:48,204
I'll have it composed for publishing.
- Wait

474
00:54:49,175 --> 00:54:53,612
Tea. . . I ordered for you too

475
00:54:53,695 --> 00:54:56,050
Sit. . . be seated

476
00:55:03,895 --> 00:55:06,284
Have a sandwich.
- No, thank you

477
00:55:07,055 --> 00:55:09,727
A sweet?
- I don't like sweets

478
00:55:13,935 --> 00:55:15,812
Shall I ask for grams?

479
00:55:16,455 --> 00:55:18,889
No, tea will be enough

480
00:55:33,455 --> 00:55:35,173
Powercut

481
00:55:39,055 --> 00:55:41,615
Dark, isn't it?
- Yes

482
00:55:42,335 --> 00:55:44,849
Let me get a candle.
- Wait. . .

483
00:55:45,615 --> 00:55:52,453
I think my orderly kept
matches and a candle in this drawer

484
00:56:00,575 --> 00:56:03,134
Or is it the upper one?

485
00:56:04,935 --> 00:56:06,926
Careful

486
00:56:07,855 --> 00:56:09,527
What happened?

487
00:56:11,655 --> 00:56:13,134
Sprain?

488
00:56:25,015 --> 00:56:26,846
Babli. . . ?

489
00:56:27,255 --> 00:56:30,725
I called home and I find
you aren't at home yet

490
00:56:31,215 --> 00:56:34,093
I'm kind of held up

491
00:56:35,095 --> 00:56:37,165
With work

492
00:56:37,255 --> 00:56:42,454
I would've been back by eight.
But my friend isn't here yet

493
00:56:43,895 --> 00:56:47,934
Not Bela. Rosie. She was
supposed to be here by seven thirty

494
00:56:48,015 --> 00:56:50,482
Seven thirty?

495
00:56:50,575 --> 00:56:53,931
7 : 30 ! Goodness!

496
00:56:54,015 --> 00:56:55,687
What happened?
- It's past 7 : 30

497
00:56:55,775 --> 00:56:58,369
So what?
- Nothing

498
00:56:58,895 --> 00:57:01,932
Got to put this in for composing.
It's getting late

499
00:57:06,295 --> 00:57:09,207
You make sure you're back home early

500
00:57:28,815 --> 00:57:31,966
Mr Gupta, wasn't Chuni with you?
- No

501
00:57:48,975 --> 00:57:52,092
She has the sprain. . .

502
00:57:52,375 --> 00:57:54,525
What are you saying?
- Nothing

503
00:58:04,535 --> 00:58:10,973
She has the sprain. . .

504
00:58:14,135 --> 00:58:16,285
Hey, you know me?

505
00:58:16,375 --> 00:58:18,172
Let go!

506
00:58:18,375 --> 00:58:19,933
Goodness!

507
00:58:34,335 --> 00:58:36,291
But you are wearing a frock

508
00:58:43,535 --> 00:58:49,644
Sunita-Sunita. . .

509
00:58:50,215 --> 00:58:53,605
Are you the one who had the sprain?
- Yes

510
00:58:54,295 --> 00:59:00,211
Glad to meet you !
Might a look enhance the pleasure?

511
00:59:00,295 --> 00:59:06,928
Show me your face, my love.
- I hear it's someone else. Ruby?

512
00:59:07,455 --> 00:59:14,486
Is she any girl? A girl is
no girl unless she's coy!

513
00:59:14,815 --> 00:59:22,688
Just look at you ! Been trying forever
to take a look at you, but no go. . . ?

514
00:59:22,775 --> 00:59:28,213
Reason? You're coy. That's a girl !
And that Ruby! Imposes herself on me

515
00:59:28,295 --> 00:59:30,490
Imposes. . . ?

516
00:59:31,535 --> 00:59:34,810
Perforce.
- But people say. . .

517
00:59:34,895 --> 00:59:42,654
Gossip! They malign a gentleman !
All because of Ruby! She fell for me

518
00:59:42,735 --> 00:59:47,490
Chuni Lal might be handsome.
But don't you stop being coy

519
00:59:47,695 --> 00:59:52,325
Chuni darling ! My ears are
sick of hearing Chuni-darlings

520
00:59:52,415 --> 00:59:54,849
And what a horrible voice!

521
01:00:22,735 --> 01:00:25,169
So this is the set-up

522
01:00:25,255 --> 01:00:26,654
But who is she?

523
01:00:43,655 --> 01:00:45,452
My cheek!

524
01:00:46,815 --> 01:00:50,091
Blood ! Hospital !

525
01:00:53,215 --> 01:00:57,003
Stop staring. Ask me why
I called you. - What for?

526
01:00:57,855 --> 01:01:01,245
Here. To return your money.
- For only this?

527
01:01:01,615 --> 01:01:02,763
Only

528
01:01:05,055 --> 01:01:07,888
May I stop the cab and get off?

529
01:01:10,455 --> 01:01:12,093
Am I to leave now?

530
01:01:16,415 --> 01:01:17,689
Sure

531
01:01:21,495 --> 01:01:24,248
What happened?
- How are you concerned?

532
01:01:25,295 --> 01:01:30,005
You want to leave? Just go on.
- But why are you in tears?

533
01:01:30,415 --> 01:01:34,294
Crying over my foolishness!
I should've posted you the money

534
01:01:34,615 --> 01:01:36,606
Why did I have to scour your
village in the midsummer sun?

535
01:01:36,695 --> 01:01:40,973
I could've left the money there
for you. Why did I leave a note?

536
01:01:41,055 --> 01:01:45,207
Why did I call you here and wait
for you so long? Why, why and why?

537
01:01:47,495 --> 01:01:49,929
Worth wondering. Why?

538
01:01:50,175 --> 01:01:51,449
Perhaps. . .

539
01:01:52,695 --> 01:01:56,370
Goodness! Could I be. . .

540
01:01:57,175 --> 01:01:59,086
in that with you?
- That. . . ?

541
01:02:00,895 --> 01:02:06,049
Love!
- Looks somewhat like that

542
01:02:06,695 --> 01:02:08,128
No!

543
01:02:13,415 --> 01:02:18,853
Bela is in love with someone.
She says, when he touches her. . .

544
01:02:19,775 --> 01:02:24,166
her whole body is electrified.
Touch me

545
01:02:25,495 --> 01:02:28,055
Happened?
- Nothing

546
01:02:28,215 --> 01:02:30,934
Thank your stars!
You're saved ! Else. . .

547
01:02:49,815 --> 01:02:52,727
This time. . . something happened?

548
01:02:56,735 --> 01:02:58,327
Stop

549
01:03:31,335 --> 01:03:35,806
Don't stare
- I will. Even in my dreams

550
01:03:42,335 --> 01:03:44,929
I'm in a fix.
- Why?

551
01:03:45,135 --> 01:03:48,093
Because you're a drunkard.
How will I face the world?

552
01:03:49,495 --> 01:03:53,328
I'm neither a drunk, nor Chuni Lal.
- Then. . . ?

553
01:03:53,415 --> 01:03:57,328
My name's Jitendra.
- Sushma's uncle?

554
01:03:57,415 --> 01:04:00,532
Yes. Surely you can face
the whole world on that?

555
01:04:30,775 --> 01:04:36,805
''Tell the world. . . ''

556
01:04:37,055 --> 01:04:38,966
''I fell in love. . . ''

557
01:04:39,255 --> 01:04:42,327
''because I was scared''

558
01:04:42,695 --> 01:04:47,052
''Alas, I am in love''

559
01:05:19,855 --> 01:05:23,325
''Let the world be jealous''

560
01:05:23,695 --> 01:05:25,765
''Our story is written''

561
01:05:25,855 --> 01:05:29,165
''We won't be afraid''

562
01:05:30,975 --> 01:05:34,683
''Hearts we have traded of love''

563
