''because I was scared''

581
01:07:01,815 --> 01:07:06,047
''Alas, I am in love''

582
01:07:27,575 --> 01:07:29,087
Who's that?

583
01:07:29,175 --> 01:07:33,009
Where's Jitu?
- Don't even mention him!

584
01:07:33,655 --> 01:07:37,045
Why are you looking away? Turn around

585
01:07:37,135 --> 01:07:40,013
It's sultry

586
01:07:40,415 --> 01:07:45,330
And the breeze is blowing this way

587
01:07:45,415 --> 01:07:50,535
And these long plantain
leaves swaying in the breeze

588
01:07:55,375 --> 01:07:57,605
Ma, look at this

589
01:07:59,975 --> 01:08:01,931
What are those three
lines on your cheek?

590
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:10,170
You see, I revere these godmen.

591
01:08:10,255 --> 01:08:14,885
Today, I met one on the way

592
01:08:15,175 --> 01:08:18,212
One of those who say ''Alakh Niranjan''

593
01:08:18,295 --> 01:08:20,126
He was walking

594
01:08:21,575 --> 01:08:25,568
I stooped to touch his feet,
but he got it wrong

595
01:08:25,814 --> 01:08:28,647
He lunged at me with his trident.
Lucky for me, I took it on the cheek

596
01:08:28,734 --> 01:08:30,929
Could've been the eye. . .

597
01:08:32,335 --> 01:08:36,010
It wasn't a godman. He was
about to fall at a woman's feet

598
01:08:36,095 --> 01:08:39,929
Don't you force me to open my mouth.
I'll use my foulest, in front of Didi

599
01:08:40,015 --> 01:08:42,575
Fighting again?
- He, not I

600
01:08:42,654 --> 01:08:47,011
Snake! He's trying to malign me!
The whole world knows. . .

601
01:08:47,095 --> 01:08:53,694
Chuni Lal won't even let a female get
close. And he tells her I'm a Casanova

602
01:08:53,774 --> 01:08:56,163
Whom?
- Sunita

603
01:08:56,455 --> 01:08:59,127
To become Chuni Lal,
you got to be born again

604
01:08:59,215 --> 01:09:04,812
The very name bowled her over!
But how do I face the world?

605
01:09:04,895 --> 01:09:10,970
They'll say, Chuni Lal is
after girls! I should drown myself

606
01:09:11,135 --> 01:09:12,807
Not even in my dreams will
I ever see your face!

607
01:09:12,895 --> 01:09:16,524
If ever, I'll wake myself up

608
01:09:16,615 --> 01:09:20,050
End of the friendship! Out of my way!

609
01:09:21,455 --> 01:09:25,448
Let him be, Didi.
He'll be fine tomorrow

610
01:09:26,455 --> 01:09:29,492
Yes. . . ?
- Sunita came to see you?

611
01:09:30,095 --> 01:09:33,212
I liked Sunita very much.
When is she coming again?

612
01:09:33,295 --> 01:09:35,091
Go and play

613
01:09:51,495 --> 01:09:58,606
Lofty ideal. And I swear by it.
I always lend the other cheek

614
01:10:00,375 --> 01:10:02,491
At your service

615
01:10:03,295 --> 01:10:08,369
If you have any anger left,
you can take it out on this cheek

616
01:10:09,215 --> 01:10:11,775
Come on, Ruby.
- Don't you dare Ruby me

617
01:10:11,855 --> 01:10:15,325
Will it be the surname, Ms Chatterjee?

618
01:10:21,215 --> 01:10:23,126
Let's go
- Listen. . .

619
01:10:38,415 --> 01:10:44,934
''Calcutta girls don't get angry.
This matter is no better''

620
01:10:47,815 --> 01:10:52,570
''Listen Ms Chatterjee,
this is a matter of my heart''

621
01:11:46,215 --> 01:11:50,527
''All dressed up and
going somewhere at 50 mph?''

622
01:11:52,855 --> 01:11:57,133
''Don't you make romantic
souls jump out of running cars''

623
01:12:08,535 --> 01:12:14,690
''On your way out, read
my heart's open letter''

624
01:12:41,055 --> 01:12:45,367
''Tear up that letter in your heart''

625
01:12:45,455 --> 01:12:49,209
''You think you can make a fool of me?''

626
01:12:58,295 --> 01:13:02,527
''You swore you love me''

627
01:13:02,615 --> 01:13:06,494
''And you go fishing?''

628
01:13:06,935 --> 01:13:12,089
''You tell me now, what is the matter?''

629
01:13:53,415 --> 01:13:57,852
''Don't you try to evade me''

630
01:13:59,975 --> 01:14:04,685
''I'll strangle
myself on your red veil''

631
01:14:15,655 --> 01:14:21,844
''But before I die, I'll
write a letter to the government''

632
01:14:59,015 --> 01:15:01,404
Be seated. I'll inform the lady

633
01:15:29,935 --> 01:15:31,414
You. . . ?

634
01:15:36,335 --> 01:15:38,291
Here on business. . . ?

635
01:15:39,415 --> 01:15:41,485
No, I was just. . .

636
01:15:41,655 --> 01:15:46,045
Working on a holiday? Or
did you want to see me?

637
01:15:46,575 --> 01:15:50,965
I didn't know you live here.
- Then what brings you here?

638
01:15:51,055 --> 01:15:52,568
Didi. . .

639
01:15:54,615 --> 01:15:57,129
She's like a tempest!

640
01:15:57,495 --> 01:16:00,487
This is my naughty sister, Babli

641
01:16:00,575 --> 01:16:03,532
Our news editor, Mr Gupta

642
01:16:06,295 --> 01:16:09,526
Never seen him before. . .
- How could you. . . ?

643
01:16:09,615 --> 01:16:12,492
He's here for the first time

644
01:16:13,375 --> 01:16:15,809
Please. . . be seated

645
01:16:24,015 --> 01:16:26,927
Yes, you never told me,
what brings you here. . .

646
01:16:27,455 --> 01:16:28,934
I. . .

647
01:16:30,255 --> 01:16:32,166
It's so hot today

648
01:16:32,255 --> 01:16:39,525
Visiting one of our neighbours?
- Yes. A friend

649
01:16:39,615 --> 01:16:43,210
I was looking for his address
when I found out that you live here

650
01:16:43,375 --> 01:16:46,924
I. . . ?
- No, your sister

651
01:16:47,695 --> 01:16:53,246
So you wanted to see my sister?
My sister's such a darling, no. . . ?

652
01:16:56,055 --> 01:16:59,809
Some tea for you?
- No thanks

653
01:17:00,895 --> 01:17:05,923
Mr Gupta, how many children have you?

654
01:17:09,055 --> 01:17:13,685
Have you. . . ?
- No. Not married yet

655
01:17:15,895 --> 01:17:18,967
You don't like the idea of marrying?

656
01:17:20,815 --> 01:17:24,490
Didn't. Until lately that is

657
01:17:25,535 --> 01:17:27,366
Have you chosen a girl for yourself?

658
01:17:30,015 --> 01:17:35,851
Next, you will surely ask
who it is? I don't mind saying

659
01:17:36,655 --> 01:17:41,968
Weren't you playing the piano?
- En passant

660
01:17:42,895 --> 01:17:48,367
En passant? Playing the
piano isn't easy, is it?

661
01:17:48,895 --> 01:17:53,366
She thinks no one can play it better
than she does. You teach her a lesson

662
01:17:54,455 --> 01:17:56,411
He'll play the piano?

663
01:17:58,935 --> 01:18:00,732
Let me try

664
01:18:42,495 --> 01:18:49,412
''I see your face in a new light''

665
