689
01:23:10,215 --> 01:23:17,485
''Your eyes must be saying something?''

690
01:23:17,695 --> 01:23:25,009
''If I'm swayed, am I at fault?''

691
01:23:43,735 --> 01:23:46,885
Not just the music. A lot of
heart went into that song. For whom?

692
01:23:48,775 --> 01:23:50,571
For you. . . ?

693
01:23:52,855 --> 01:23:58,964
May I leave now, Ms Amita?
- Today's a holiday. Leave after lunch

694
01:23:59,055 --> 01:24:02,730
Thanks, some other time. As I told you,
I have an appointment with a friend

695
01:24:02,815 --> 01:24:04,931
I'm rather late. Bye

696
01:24:07,535 --> 01:24:12,005
Wait. . . let the car drop you.
- I'll tell the chauffeur

697
01:24:19,215 --> 01:24:24,130
Who was this?
- Mr Jitendra Gupta

698
01:24:31,655 --> 01:24:34,931
The Chinese have attacked.
Buy up everything

699
01:24:35,335 --> 01:24:37,849
We'll sell
everything on the black-market

700
01:24:38,655 --> 01:24:44,093
Only if the war deepens. In
the last war, we made millions

701
01:24:44,815 --> 01:24:47,169
This time, we'll make tenfold

702
01:24:47,415 --> 01:24:50,691
Sunita, you might've
heard of the Chinese attack

703
01:24:50,775 --> 01:24:53,242
I'm leaving for Tejpur?
- Tejpur. . . ?

704
01:24:53,335 --> 01:24:57,044
Yes Tejpur. If I get permission,
I'll go right to the front

705
01:24:57,335 --> 01:25:00,930
No! You can't go there.
Send someone else

706
01:25:01,215 --> 01:25:03,934
I told the editor, I'm going myself

707
01:25:04,855 --> 01:25:08,210
Nearly time for the flight.
I won't be able to see you

708
01:25:08,295 --> 01:25:11,731
I'll see you when I get back.
- No! I'm not letting you go

709
01:25:13,855 --> 01:25:18,565
What's up? Why are you so disturbed?
- You know Didi. . .

710
01:25:18,855 --> 01:25:22,530
Don't you leave without seeing me.
- Who's going? Where?

711
01:25:23,855 --> 01:25:28,485
Friend of mine. Leaving Calcutta.
I must see her

712
01:25:32,815 --> 01:25:35,204
What's come over you? Take the call

713
01:25:39,175 --> 01:25:40,449
One minute

714
01:25:40,535 --> 01:25:42,173
For you

715
01:25:46,495 --> 01:25:48,644
Yes Mr Shukla

716
01:25:51,495 --> 01:25:54,931
What did you say? Mr Gupta is going?

717
01:25:55,695 --> 01:25:59,324
No! How did you take such a
big decision without my say-so?

718
01:25:59,415 --> 01:26:03,374
I tried to convince Mr
Gupta about sending a reporter

719
01:26:03,455 --> 01:26:07,004
But he said he was sure,
you'd let him go

720
01:26:07,095 --> 01:26:11,930
Never! I mean, stop him.
I'll come and decide who goes

721
01:26:22,135 --> 01:26:25,923
Chini Lal? Not Chini Lal. Chuni Lal

722
01:26:26,015 --> 01:26:31,772
Chuni Lal has ''chini''
( sugar) every morning with tea

723
01:26:35,295 --> 01:26:39,413
Not even a smile? Fought
with your wife this morning?

724
01:26:48,695 --> 01:26:52,210
Where's Mr Gupta?
- I went to stop him. . .

725
01:26:52,295 --> 01:26:54,286
as soon as you told me.
- And. . . ?

726
01:26:54,375 --> 01:26:56,684
But. . .
- Where is he?

727
01:26:56,775 --> 01:26:59,687
He had left already.
- Left already?

728
01:26:59,775 --> 01:27:05,644
You know how important his presence
is for me. . . for the newspaper

729
01:27:06,575 --> 01:27:09,452
Why did you give him the
chance to endanger his life?

730
01:27:09,935 --> 01:27:12,574
Don't leave! Please! Stay,
for my sake!

731
01:27:13,455 --> 01:27:17,050
Or tell me you don't love me.
- I do

732
01:27:18,055 --> 01:27:21,172
But I also love my
country and my profession

733
01:27:21,255 --> 01:27:24,884
The Army is there to save
the country. Why are you going?

734
01:27:24,975 --> 01:27:30,766
To tell my countrymen how
bravely they fight the enemy

735
01:27:31,455 --> 01:27:35,242
After all it's for us
that the Army is fighting

736
01:27:35,335 --> 01:27:39,169
Until we back our Army to the last,
our independence is at stake

737
01:27:39,535 --> 01:27:46,213
That maybe so. But my
heart doesn't permit me. . .

738
01:27:46,495 --> 01:27:51,649
Silly! Nothing's going to happen
to me. Send me away with a smile

739
01:28:55,534 --> 01:29:02,451
''With a smile he greeted me''

740
01:29:02,934 --> 01:29:08,850
''I thought it was love''

741
01:29:09,094 --> 01:29:15,169
''Oh so mistaken I was''

742
01:29:15,254 --> 01:29:21,284
''I thought it was an
expression of amour''

743
01:29:46,254 --> 01:29:52,409
''I wasn't destined to have someone. . .

744
01:29:52,494 --> 01:29:58,250
''I could call my own''

745
01:30:23,414 --> 01:30:29,125
''Oh why did I think. . . ''

746
01:30:29,574 --> 01:30:35,285
''I deserve love?''

747
01:31:00,214 --> 01:31:06,210
''Oh how can I weep?''

748
01:31:06,454 --> 01:31:12,643
''Oh how do I speak?''

749
01:31:37,534 --> 01:31:43,404
''I'm afraid. . . ''

750
01:31:43,694 --> 01:31:49,564
''for the conclusion
the world might jump to''

751
01:31:50,014 --> 01:31:55,805
''I was mistaken. . . ''

752
01:31:56,294 --> 01:32:02,050
''I thought it was an
expression of amour''

753
01:32:02,294 --> 01:32:07,925
''With a smile he greeted me''

754
01:32:08,214 --> 01:32:14,369
''I thought it was love''

755
01:32:29,854 --> 01:32:33,927
What is the matter Didi? Your eyes. . .
- No, it's nothing of the sort

756
01:32:35,934 --> 01:32:40,928
My eyes are a bit fatigued

757
01:32:43,294 --> 01:32:48,652
Another sleepless night?
- I'm anxious, Didi

758
01:32:50,334 --> 01:32:55,727
Anxiety? Because of the war?
- Are you anxious too?

759
01:32:55,814 --> 01:32:58,931
Me. . . ? Well. . .

760
01:32:59,734 --> 01:33:01,406
Tell me

761
01:33:03,334 --> 01:33:06,849
Everyone's anxious, Babli.
Go to sleep

762
01:33:08,854 --> 01:33:12,688
I'm so anxious,
Didi ! Oh I'm so anxious

763
01:33:13,574 --> 01:33:17,009
You don't know who might die!
- What are you saying?

764
01:33:17,094 --> 01:33:20,769
Silly! Don't bring these
things to your mind. Don't!

765
01:33:20,854 --> 01:33:23,732
Didi, why are you so worked up?

766
01:33:25,294 --> 01:33:30,971
I. . . For your sake,
Babli. You were in tears

767
01:33:31,814 --> 01:33:36,842
I hate wars. It makes me cry.

768
01:33:38,214 --> 01:33:41,206
Tears sometimes are a blessing

769
01:33:42,094 --> 01:33:44,369
What do I do?

770
01:33:44,814 --> 01:33:51,287
I can't cry, I can't laugh.
Go to sleep

771
01:34:11,334 --> 01:34:15,849
Captain, I hear this
bridge was built only last year

772
01:34:16,574 --> 01:34:18,212
How come it has collapsed so soon?

773
01:34:18,294 --> 01:34:22,048
Under the weight of
refugees crossing

774
01:34:24,334 --> 01:34:29,692
An incident like this in times of
war? Could it be a traitor's work?

775
01:34:29,774 --> 01:34:35,963
Traitors are what we should call them.
Those who built it, used bad cement

776
01:34:37,574 --> 01:34:39,690
Adulterated cement?

777
01:34:40,894 --> 01:34:46,810
I must expose those who
have betrayed the country

778
01:35:12,094 --> 01:35:13,447
Read that?

779
01:35:15,494 --> 01:35:18,133
And it's our
newspaper that publishes it

780
01:35:19,174 --> 01:35:22,484
Must be mere suspicion.
How can they find evidence?

781
01:35:22,574 --> 01:35:27,364
That fool Jitendra Gupta is out there.
He might've unearthed some evidence

782
01:35:31,214 --> 01:35:34,843
I have the key to his silence

783
01:35:35,454 --> 01:35:40,244
News from Tejpur brings hope.
Our forces have put up. . .

784
01:35:40,334 --> 01:35:43,053
a determined resistance
against the Chinese aggressors. . .

785
01:35:43,134 --> 01:35:47,446
forcing the Chinese
into retreat at Tejpur

786
01:35:47,534 --> 01:35:49,445
A ceasefire has been announced

787
01:35:49,614 --> 01:35:52,253
Hello Didi.
- Hello Ms Amita

788
01:35:53,654 --> 01:35:59,411
You know, the Chinese are in retreat!
They didn't reach Tejpur

789
01:35:59,494 --> 01:36:02,724
That's great news!
- Great news!

790
01:36:03,374 --> 01:36:07,969
I can't tell you
what great news this is!

791
01:36:09,374 --> 01:36:11,808
She's so happy! This is your chance!

792
01:36:11,894 --> 01:36:14,249
Say it. Shoot
- Shut up

793
01:36:16,254 --> 01:36:19,212
Did you say something?
- No.

794
01:36:19,294 --> 01:36:21,364
Why don't you say it?
- What is the matter?

795
01:36:22,694 --> 01:36:28,326
Bikram has been
pestering me to tell you that. . .

796
01:36:28,414 --> 01:36:31,929
You won't ever say it! Let me say it

797
01:36:32,454 --> 01:36:35,173
Didi, I want to marry Babli

798
01:36:37,614 --> 01:36:39,172
What. . . ?

799
01:36:40,734 --> 01:36:44,727
No, you can't marry Babli

800
01:36:45,534 --> 01:36:47,125
Why not?

801
01:36:47,974 --> 01:36:52,525
I thought you loved me like a
brother. - That may be so. But. . .

802
01:36:53,574 --> 01:36:58,728
I want to see Babli happy.
- Babli will be very happy with me

803
01:36:58,814 --> 01:37:02,284
I'm certain !
- No, you are mistaken

804
01:37:04,094 --> 01:37:07,928
How come. . . ?
- Is she in love with someone else?

805
01:37:09,574 --> 01:37:14,409
No. . . she has told me nothing.
- Then you know something?

806
01:37:14,854 --> 01:37:16,845
Is there anyone else in her life?

807
01:37:16,934 --> 01:37:20,483
Didi, I want to listen to the radio

808
01:37:22,134 --> 01:37:25,649
Your sister was saying. . .
- Never mind. Go on

809
01:37:35,014 --> 01:37:39,644
We could've found out from her.
Why did you send her away?

810
01:37:40,494 --> 01:37:44,726
I don't think I'm answerable to you.
All I'm telling you is. . .

811
01:37:45,774 --> 01:37:49,244
as long as I'm alive, you
won't marry Babli. Never

812
01:37:50,254 --> 01:37:55,692
I know why! You don't want
your sister to be loved.

813
01:37:55,894 --> 01:37:59,682
Because, for yourself you
haven't had a man's love

814
01:38:01,614 --> 01:38:04,128
I apologise on his behalf

815
01:38:04,214 --> 01:38:06,648
Fool ! Get out of here

816
01:38:16,134 --> 01:38:20,764
You haven't had a man's love

817
01:38:30,574 --> 01:38:32,690
Hello Ms Amita

818
01:38:39,294 --> 01:38:43,889
You might be surprised
seeing me here. I've just returned

819
01:38:45,294 --> 01:38:46,773
Be seated

820
01:38:53,894 --> 01:38:57,011
My suspicions about the
bridge turns out to be true

821
01:38:57,094 --> 01:39:01,451
I've found the evidence.
I want to do a series of articles

822
01:39:01,894 --> 01:39:03,930
Do that

823
01:39:04,014 --> 01:39:09,134
Think it over, Ms Amita. The person
who supplied adulterated cement. . .

824
01:39:09,214 --> 01:39:12,172
is your partner in the paper

825
01:39:14,774 --> 01:39:17,925
I have no partners

826
01:39:19,334 --> 01:39:21,973
For the sake of the truth,
publish whatever you want

827
01:39:23,294 --> 01:39:24,773
I'm with you

828
01:39:31,214 --> 01:39:34,092
I mean Mr Gupta, when
did you return from Tejpur?

829
01:39:34,174 --> 01:39:35,607
Today

830
01:39:37,374 --> 01:39:42,402
Didi. . . I knew he went there.
Now who told me. . . ?

831
01:39:42,974 --> 01:39:47,889
Who else? I might've been the one?

832
01:39:48,774 --> 01:39:51,686
Yes Didi ! You were the one

833
01:39:52,334 --> 01:39:56,043
Sit
- What a lovely day!

834
01:39:56,534 --> 01:39:58,411
Lovely weather

835
01:39:59,094 --> 01:40:01,005
Isn't that so, Mr Gupta?
- Oh yes

836
01:40:02,134 --> 01:40:04,090
Beautiful weather

837
01:40:04,174 --> 01:40:07,962
Let's go out somewhere,
Didi ! Oh, but how can you?

838
01:40:08,054 --> 01:40:14,402
You got to go to the office. Mr Gupta,
my sister likes nothing but work

839
01:40:17,014 --> 01:40:22,407
Liking anything else is no good,
Babli. One ends up a loser

840
01:40:23,614 --> 01:40:27,447
Go on, take a day out.
- I'll leave after lunch

841
01:40:27,694 --> 01:40:29,685
But where. . . ?

842
01:40:31,094 --> 01:40:33,562
Where should I go, Mr Gupta?

843
01:40:33,654 --> 01:40:37,772
Wherever you feel like.
- Just go somewhere

844
01:40:39,814 --> 01:40:44,524
Mr Gupta, you must be tired.
You can join office from tomorrow

845
01:40:46,094 --> 01:40:48,005
The fish ! Brilliant!

846
01:40:48,294 --> 01:40:50,888
I love gazing at fish

847
01:40:51,094 --> 01:40:55,531
The lake at botanical gardens is full
of fish. I'm going there after lunch

848
01:41:08,574 --> 01:41:16,571
''At heart I was always ecstatic''

849
01:41:17,054 --> 01:41:25,007
''You've added to it a dash of madness''

850
01:41:58,854 --> 01:42:06,363
''There's a bit of
craziness in our age''

851
01:42:07,134 --> 01:42:14,893
''And some of it, because we're young''

852
01:42:19,694 --> 01:42:27,612
''And it puts a fire in our my breath''

853
01:42:28,134 --> 01:42:36,132
''And you've added to
it a dash of madness''

854
01:42:53,054 --> 01:43:00,369
''True, at this moment,
I'm not in my senses''

855
01:43:01,334 --> 01:43:09,048
''In the ecstasy,
I might swoon in your arms''

856
01:43:17,974 --> 01:43:26,052
''Those eyes have devoured me''

857
01:43:26,374 --> 01:43:34,644
''At heart I was always ecstatic''

858
01:43:42,934 --> 01:43:50,966
''These dancing tresses,
this fiery beauty''

859
01:43:59,574 --> 01:44:07,491
''Oh stop yourself, please''

860
01:44:12,174 --> 01:44:20,127
''My emotions are caught in a storm''

861
01:44:20,614 --> 01:44:28,248
''You've added to it a dash of madness''

862
01:44:28,934 --> 01:44:36,887
''At heart I was always ecstatic''

863
01:44:44,974 --> 01:44:46,248
Welcome

864
01:44:46,334 --> 01:44:50,964
Forgive me for interrupting.
- I have the whole day ahead

865
01:44:51,054 --> 01:44:54,091
This article has to
be in by this evening

866
01:44:55,214 --> 01:44:59,253
About the cement factory?
- Yes, please have a seat

867
01:44:59,334 --> 01:45:01,563
No thanks, I got to get back early

868
01:45:03,414 --> 01:45:07,326
Early this morning, the owners of
the cement factory paid me a visit

869
01:45:09,254 --> 01:45:12,326
They want me to ask Ms
Amita to have you fired

870
01:45:15,774 --> 01:45:18,652
Then you should've
gone to Ms Amita directly

871
01:45:21,574 --> 01:45:25,361
How I wish you understood me
as well as I understand you

872
01:45:26,094 --> 01:45:31,043
I come in hope. Hoping that you will
never do a disservice to Ms Amita

873
01:45:31,494 --> 01:45:34,884
How can she get hurt?

874
01:45:36,334 --> 01:45:39,565
This newspaper earlier operated
from the small building next door

875
01:45:40,694 --> 01:45:45,051
This new building, all
this new machinery. . .

876
01:45:45,334 --> 01:45:49,566
the rise of this newspaper is
all by dint of Ms Amita's efforts

877
01:45:50,294 --> 01:45:53,206
For which, she has had
to borrow in millions

878
01:45:53,374 --> 01:45:57,606
From whom?
- The very men who want you out

879
01:45:57,694 --> 01:46:00,049
Ms Amita's entire
shareholding is mortgaged to them

880
01:46:00,134 --> 01:46:01,965
And the term of the
loan is running out

881
01:46:02,454 --> 01:46:08,005
So if they want, they
can also throw Ms Amita out

882
01:46:08,094 --> 01:46:11,643
I came to tell you just that.
I leave the decision to you

883
01:46:12,694 --> 01:46:17,210
I am sure whatever you
do will be for the best

884
01:46:28,174 --> 01:46:31,564
No! Mr Gupta doesn't leave!

885
01:46:32,654 --> 01:46:37,250
Is this your final decision?
- Absolutely

886
01:46:44,134 --> 01:46:47,683
Forgive us, we have troubled you

887
01:46:59,174 --> 01:47:02,849
You're making a grave mistake

888
01:47:04,094 --> 01:47:08,406
The paper shouldn't pass
into their hands, come what may

889
01:47:08,934 --> 01:47:13,246
You want me to accept their dictate?

890
01:47:13,334 --> 01:47:16,291
What option is there?

891
01:47:16,374 --> 01:47:18,808
You say, your entire
stock is mortgaged to them

892
01:47:18,894 --> 01:47:22,011
I'm not going to be threatened !

893
01:47:22,094 --> 01:47:26,485
As long as I am, Mr Gupta stays

894
01:47:26,934 --> 01:47:32,725
For how long? If they wish,
they can have you thrown out

895
01:47:32,814 --> 01:47:35,203
Will Mr Gupta be able
to survive afterwards?

896
01:47:35,294 --> 01:47:39,684
Come what may, he will leave. Why
should you leave your newspaper?

897
01:47:39,774 --> 01:47:46,009
But how can I throw out
someone who is innocent? Never!

898
01:47:46,614 --> 01:47:52,052
Must you be so adamant? In your
life this newspaper meant everything !

899
01:47:52,134 --> 01:47:54,250
Today, you don't care?

900
01:47:55,254 --> 01:47:57,404
Does Mr Gupta mean more to you?

901
01:47:57,734 --> 01:48:00,646
Give me an answer!
For the sake of what. . .

902
01:48:00,734 --> 01:48:04,170
are you determined to ruin your
newspaper, your future, your life?

903
01:48:04,454 --> 01:48:06,763
Why can't you fire Mr Gupta?

904
01:48:07,654 --> 01:48:12,933
I won't! I won't fire him!

905
01:48:15,054 --> 01:48:19,013
Why, I ask you ! What reason
is it that's stopping you?

906
01:48:19,094 --> 01:48:22,166
What comes over you at the
mention that he might have to leave?

907
01:48:23,174 --> 01:48:27,452
Could it be that you have
a soft corner for Mr Gupta?

908
01:48:33,054 --> 01:48:39,004
Then my suspicion is true.
You are in love with Mr Gupta

909
01:49:21,694 --> 01:49:28,167
They want to throw you out! Just let
them try! We'll raze this building !

910
01:49:28,934 --> 01:49:32,006
Oh but this is all stone. . .
we'll raze it nevertheless

911
01:49:32,094 --> 01:49:35,973
We'll go on strike, red flags and all !

912
01:49:36,054 --> 01:49:39,330
One of the union leaders
shares a tipple with me

913
01:49:39,414 --> 01:49:42,371
All I got to do is ply him some,
and we have a blockade

914
01:49:42,454 --> 01:49:44,683
Madam is in her office

915
01:49:46,534 --> 01:49:49,001
Where are you going? Listen. . .

916
01:49:50,534 --> 01:49:54,924
I'm no Chuni Lal unless I
fix each and everyone of them

917
01:49:55,014 --> 01:50:01,203
I'll take a photo his folks won't
recognise, forget his neighbours!

918
01:50:05,894 --> 01:50:07,293
Ms Amita. . .

919
01:50:16,934 --> 01:50:19,812
What's this?
- My resignation

920
01:50:22,494 --> 01:50:24,212
Resignation?

921
01:50:24,454 --> 01:50:30,483
Yes. I'm quitting.
- Why?

922
01:50:31,374 --> 01:50:34,605
Till yesterday, you were happy here.
Why, all of a sudden. . . ?

923
01:50:34,694 --> 01:50:40,007
Nothing. I just want to leave.
- Tell me the truth

924
01:50:40,454 --> 01:50:45,130
Has the cement lobby threatened you?
Are you doing this for me?

925
01:50:45,814 --> 01:50:50,763
For the newspaper. More than me,
this newspaper needs you

926
01:50:50,854 --> 01:50:52,287
But. . .

927
01:50:55,374 --> 01:50:57,490
I can't run this paper all alone

928
01:50:58,214 --> 01:51:02,001
You aren't leaving.
- Please appoint another news editor

929
01:51:02,374 --> 01:51:06,844
Why get into trouble for my sake?
Please, let me leave

930
01:51:08,414 --> 01:51:14,933
You are being uselessly stubborn.
Take your resignation back

931
01:51:15,734 --> 01:51:21,730
I'm helpless, Ms Amita. My ego
won't let me work here anymore

932
01:51:21,814 --> 01:51:25,648
All you care for is your own ego?
What about someone else?

933
01:51:29,494 --> 01:51:32,929
The managing director's
words hold no meaning for you?

934
01:51:33,014 --> 01:51:37,690
I don't get any of this. My departure
will help keep your newspaper afloat

935
01:51:37,774 --> 01:51:39,765
What else is your problem?
- Don't trouble me anymore!

936
01:51:39,854 --> 01:51:43,369
For God's sake! I don't accept
your resignation ! You aren't leaving

937
01:51:43,614 --> 01:51:49,883
You aren't and you aren't!
- Irrespective, I'm leaving

938
01:52:22,414 --> 01:52:26,532
Are you going somewhere?
- Yes

939
01:52:29,414 --> 01:52:31,132
At night. . . ?

940
01:52:32,374 --> 01:52:33,523
Where?

941
01:52:36,254 --> 01:52:38,131
I'm leaving this house

942
01:52:45,494 --> 01:52:48,611
Come off it! Give me that suitcase.
- No Didi

943
01:52:49,654 --> 01:52:51,167
No. . . ?

944
01:52:51,654 --> 01:52:56,125
You won't obey your sister?
- No! I've always been afraid of you

945
01:52:56,214 --> 01:52:59,047
But you don't scare
me anymore! Get that?

946
01:53:02,174 --> 01:53:07,043
What's all this happening?

947
01:53:09,494 --> 01:53:12,531
Why are you misunderstanding me?

948
01:53:13,974 --> 01:53:20,163
If I ever said anything untoward,
it's for your own good, Babli

949
01:53:20,254 --> 01:53:23,769
I'll be the judge of that, Didi.
I'm not a kid anymore

950
01:53:23,934 --> 01:53:27,370
Think of your own good,
think of your life

951
01:53:27,654 --> 01:53:35,493
My life is for you.
What have I left but you?

952
01:53:38,854 --> 01:53:43,291
If you leave me, this
loneliness will drive me mad, Babli !

953
01:53:43,374 --> 01:53:47,286
It'll drive me mad !
- Who's asking you to be lonely?

954
01:53:47,374 --> 01:53:49,126
Why don't you marry?

955
01:53:52,974 --> 01:53:55,442
Marry. . . ?
- Yes. Get married

956
01:53:55,534 --> 01:53:59,163
How long will I give you company?
Everyone wants to make a family

957
01:53:59,254 --> 01:54:01,688
I too want a home of my own

958
01:54:05,374 --> 01:54:07,934
Babli, sit

959
01:54:11,534 --> 01:54:14,651
You needn't leave home over this

960
01:54:15,014 --> 01:54:21,533
I'll get you married to the man
you want. I'll give whatever you want

961
01:54:22,334 --> 01:54:26,009
Yes, whatever you want.
- Then let me leave

962
01:54:27,814 --> 01:54:32,968
Are you too shy to tell me?
I know where you want to go

963
01:54:33,774 --> 01:54:36,891
I know whom you want to marry.
- You are mistaken

964
01:54:36,974 --> 01:54:41,092
Don't you lie to me.
- You're so old-fashioned

965
01:54:41,174 --> 01:54:45,087
Talking to a man, laughing with him,
doesn't mean I'm in love with him

966
01:54:45,174 --> 01:54:48,325
Try as you might, you
aren't deceiving your sister

967
01:54:48,654 --> 01:54:50,326
You may assume
whatever you wish. I'm leaving

968
01:54:50,574 --> 01:54:56,205
Babli ! I'm not letting you leave!
Never! Tell me the truth !

969
01:54:56,294 --> 01:55:00,606
Why do you want to leave?
- Because you've lost your senses

970
01:55:00,854 --> 01:55:03,766
You want to force Jiten
upon me! Let go of my hand

971
01:55:03,854 --> 01:55:08,803
No Babli ! No! Don't
go away! I beg of you !

972
01:55:08,894 --> 01:55:13,046
Oh why do you hate me?
Babli, have pity on your sister!

973
01:55:13,134 --> 01:55:16,126
Babli ! Stop! For my sake!

974
01:55:36,014 --> 01:55:37,732
What happened?

975
01:55:45,334 --> 01:55:47,325
Babli went away

976
01:55:48,814 --> 01:55:55,606
She too is gone. . .
leaving me all alone

977
01:55:58,214 --> 01:56:00,330
Uncle, Ms Sunita is here

978
01:56:09,254 --> 01:56:11,893
You. . . ? So late at night?

979
01:56:18,774 --> 01:56:23,450
What's the mater Sunita?
Is Ms Amita all right?

980
01:56:26,014 --> 01:56:27,413
Didi. . . ?

981
01:56:28,254 --> 01:56:32,041
She looked harried today.
I was concerned

982
01:56:37,534 --> 01:56:44,212
You care for Didi?
- Who wouldn't? Why do you ask?

983
01:56:46,174 --> 01:56:49,644
She's fine.

984
01:56:50,974 --> 01:56:54,364
You must take care of her always.
Else, I'll quarrel with you

985
01:56:54,454 --> 01:56:57,844
What are you saying? What
has come over you today?

986
01:57:01,214 --> 01:57:02,488
Today. . .

987
01:57:04,534 --> 01:57:06,525
today's a happy day for me

988
01:57:07,414 --> 01:57:10,451
Didi, I'm getting married tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?

989
01:57:10,894 --> 01:57:15,843
Jitu, why didn't you tell me earlier?
- Are you marrying my uncle?

990
01:57:16,854 --> 01:57:21,848
Your uncle is just a friend of mine.
The one I'm marrying, is a lovely boy

991
01:57:28,174 --> 01:57:31,689
Why are you silent?
Won't you congratulate me?

992
01:57:32,174 --> 01:57:36,452
Why not? Sushma, get some sweets

993
01:57:41,734 --> 01:57:47,809
Sunita, are you joking?
- Strange of you. . .

994
01:57:47,894 --> 01:57:52,172
to take the truth for a joke,
and you take a joke to be true?

995
01:57:54,574 --> 01:57:59,250
Look into my eyes and say it.
Everything was a joke?

996
01:58:00,214 --> 01:58:02,010
Tell me you don't love me

997
01:58:04,614 --> 01:58:09,404
Is it a must to marry everyone
one has a light romance with?

998
01:58:10,094 --> 01:58:12,813
Life is to be enjoyed.
That's all I know

999
01:58:12,894 --> 01:58:15,567
I'd hate to cry after I'm married.

1000
01:58:15,654 --> 01:58:18,327
Were you to marry me
you'd never be happy?

1001
01:58:19,814 --> 01:58:22,089
Would it be a life of misery?

1002
01:58:23,014 --> 01:58:24,732
That's my lot.

1003
01:58:25,894 --> 01:58:30,490
I've been very lucky.
I always liked a comfortable life

1004
01:58:30,934 --> 01:58:34,722
I'm marrying a millionaire

1005
01:58:35,014 --> 01:58:36,811
Congratulations

1006
01:58:36,974 --> 01:58:41,525
How come the millionaire's bride-to-be
is standing in a poor man's hovel?

1007
01:58:45,254 --> 01:58:51,773
I don't take you for an enemy.
- Thanks

1008
01:58:52,734 --> 01:58:56,932
I shall never forget this courtesy

1009
01:58:59,454 --> 01:59:01,523
I'm getting late

1010
01:59:16,694 --> 01:59:22,724
Whether you sell your
share or whether you pawn it. . .

1011
01:59:23,174 --> 01:59:27,611
you aren't mortgaging my share.

1012
01:59:29,014 --> 01:59:31,972
Just selling my shares won't
help pay back Ms Amita's debts.

1013
01:59:32,374 --> 01:59:34,092
Her debts run into millions

1014
01:59:34,454 --> 01:59:37,206
I take the responsibility.
You'll get back every cent

1015
01:59:37,694 --> 01:59:40,527
At this point of time,
you must help her

1016
01:59:45,414 --> 01:59:50,885
Help whom? The person who
wouldn't let me marry Babli?

1017
01:59:52,014 --> 01:59:53,732
Why don't you understand?

1018
01:59:53,814 --> 01:59:56,772
Helping her now will
pave the way to marry Babli.

1019
01:59:56,854 --> 01:59:59,414
I'm sure, she will be happy to oblige

1020
02:00:02,094 --> 02:00:07,532
Not afterwards. Before.
First I marry. Then I help

1021
02:00:08,574 --> 02:00:15,286
Will you cash in on this crisis?
- Give and take

1022
02:00:16,974 --> 02:00:20,410
I'm your little brother
- I'm ashamed of you !

1023
02:00:39,214 --> 02:00:41,853
Will you marry me?
- Marry. . . ?

1024
02:00:41,934 --> 02:00:43,925
Tomorrow.
- Tomorrow itself?

1025
02:00:44,014 --> 02:00:48,485
Or the day after?
- Right now! Right away!

1026
02:00:48,574 --> 02:00:51,041
Come on, let's find ourselves a priest

1027
02:00:55,134 --> 02:00:59,047
Have you run away from home?
- Yes, Hollywood style

1028
02:00:59,134 --> 02:01:02,570
Eloping is in vogue!
- Stop raving

1029
02:01:02,854 --> 02:01:06,403
I'm not about to let this happen.
How will I face your sister?

1030
02:01:07,974 --> 02:01:10,727
Just let the wedding get over.
Afterwards, I might even be willing. . .

1031
02:01:10,814 --> 02:01:13,851
to help her tide the crisis.
- What kind of crisis?

1032
02:01:15,014 --> 02:01:19,166
All because of that Jitendra Gupta.
The directors want him out

1033
02:01:19,254 --> 02:01:22,564
Simple. Throw him out.
- Why throw him out?

1034
02:01:23,094 --> 02:01:27,849
Because he's worthless.
What is he? Just a news editor

1035
02:01:28,294 --> 02:01:32,924
He has got the board warring. I don't
understand why he doesn't leave

1036
02:01:33,534 --> 02:01:35,411
I think he's a cheap fellow

1037
02:01:39,014 --> 02:01:41,369
What did I say?
- That's what you deserve

1038
02:01:41,734 --> 02:01:42,962
Come here

1039
02:01:49,094 --> 02:01:54,168
You stay away from him. You will
marry with your sister's consent

1040
02:01:54,414 --> 02:01:59,169
Not her consent. Mine!
I'm going to marry Bikram!

1041
02:02:04,214 --> 02:02:07,524
Didi's photo? In your bedroom?

1042
02:02:19,974 --> 02:02:21,612
Madam. . .

1043
02:02:28,414 --> 02:02:30,132
Mr Verma is here

1044
02:02:33,654 --> 02:02:35,133
Mr Verma

1045
02:02:49,374 --> 02:02:50,807
Ms Amita. . .

1046
02:02:56,614 --> 02:02:58,491
Are you all right?

1047
02:03:02,654 --> 02:03:07,045
Babli has gone away
and I don't know where

1048
02:03:07,214 --> 02:03:12,129
Don't worry. She's fine.
She came to my house last night

1049
02:03:13,534 --> 02:03:15,330
Your house?
- Yes

1050
02:03:15,414 --> 02:03:18,166
She wants to marry Bikram

1051
02:03:20,574 --> 02:03:22,723
Bikram. . . ?
- Yes

1052
02:03:26,974 --> 02:03:30,125
Why did she desert me for that?

1053
02:03:30,734 --> 02:03:34,522
I told her she can
marry whoever she wants

1054
02:03:35,254 --> 02:03:40,692
You said that? Then why
did she have to leave?

1055
02:03:42,054 --> 02:03:44,010
I don't understand. . .

1056
02:03:44,534 --> 02:03:49,289
if she loves Bikram,
why did she slap him?

1057
02:03:51,494 --> 02:03:56,727
What did you say? She slapped Bikram?

1058
02:03:56,814 --> 02:04:00,523
Yes, he spoke against Mr Gupta

1059
02:04:05,414 --> 02:04:07,608
Then it's true!

1060
02:04:09,294 --> 02:04:14,971
Silly girl ! Why did she lie to me?
I knew she doesn't like Bikram

1061
02:04:15,374 --> 02:04:16,932
I knew it well !

1062
02:04:17,494 --> 02:04:21,169
I'm not going to let her
ruin her life by marrying Bikram

1063
02:04:21,374 --> 02:04:24,013
Never!

1064
02:04:24,494 --> 02:04:26,803
I won't let this marriage happen

1065
02:04:34,814 --> 02:04:40,172
Not Bikram. It's me Didi. Your Babli.
Why are you so worried?

1066
02:04:41,694 --> 02:04:48,008
You ask me why I'm worried?
You're worried, how can I not be?

1067
02:04:48,334 --> 02:04:53,885
But Didi. . .
- You mustn't have slept all night

1068
02:04:55,214 --> 02:05:00,334
I did. Had a sound sleep.
- Liar

1069
02:05:01,534 --> 02:05:05,572
Did you ever have a sound sleep
unless your sister tucked you in?

1070
02:05:07,454 --> 02:05:10,889
You suffer and make
your sister suffer!

1071
02:05:11,574 --> 02:05:14,849
I'll punish you ! Just you come home

1072
02:05:17,134 --> 02:05:22,083
But Didi, listen. . .
- Not a word

1073
02:05:22,774 --> 02:05:27,928
I know. You're crying on the sly

1074
02:05:33,174 --> 02:05:37,213
Come back. . . come back to your sister

1075
02:05:40,134 --> 02:05:45,083
Coming. . . I'm coming right away.
- Hurry!

1076
02:05:45,534 --> 02:05:49,446
And tell Bikram, you
aren't marrying him

1077
02:05:50,254 --> 02:05:56,090
But I'm going to marry Bikram.
- But why?

1078
02:05:56,494 --> 02:05:59,326
Why are you out to destroy yourself?

1079
02:05:59,534 --> 02:06:02,809
You too are out to destroy
your happiness for my sake!

1080
02:06:03,174 --> 02:06:08,202
How can I let this happen?
No! I'm not coming

1081
02:06:08,614 --> 02:06:10,808
Listen Babli. . .

1082
02:06:19,094 --> 02:06:23,326
What happened?
- She won't come

1083
02:06:23,934 --> 02:06:28,610
She says, my happiness will
be destroyed if she returns

1084
02:06:28,694 --> 02:06:30,525
She said that?

1085
02:06:32,094 --> 02:06:37,248
Meaningless drivel ! Let me
see how she won't return

1086
02:06:37,574 --> 02:06:41,567
Have I not even this right?
I'm going to drag her here

1087
02:06:41,654 --> 02:06:46,091
No Ms Amita ! Stop! I know
why she's doing all this

1088
02:06:46,894 --> 02:06:50,125
She too knows that you
are in love with Mr Gupta

1089
02:06:53,134 --> 02:06:54,533
Good God !

1090
02:07:00,134 --> 02:07:07,529
The only way out. . .
then this is the only way

1091
02:07:24,534 --> 02:07:26,525
Where is she?

1092
02:07:26,614 --> 02:07:32,052
If you want to see me alive, come
back to me! Babli ! Don't hide from me!

1093
02:07:32,134 --> 02:07:33,647
Madam. . .

1094
02:07:35,574 --> 02:07:38,246
Where's Babli?

1095
02:07:38,334 --> 02:07:41,883
She went out with Mr Bikram.
She left this note for you

1096
02:07:42,694 --> 02:07:45,845
Didi, I knew you'd come here for me

1097
02:07:45,934 --> 02:07:49,324
But now it's time for you to
think of your own happiness

1098
02:07:49,654 --> 02:07:53,488
By the time you receive this letter,
I would've married Bikram

1099
02:08:06,734 --> 02:08:09,487
No. . .

1100
02:08:24,534 --> 02:08:28,686
Married already?

1101
02:08:46,774 --> 02:08:50,483
You must give a month's
notice for a civil marriage

1102
02:08:50,574 --> 02:08:53,088
Only afterwards can
I conduct the marriage

1103
02:08:53,814 --> 02:08:58,604
But we want to get married today!
- There's the law, lady

1104
02:08:58,854 --> 02:09:01,607
I'm a government registrar.
Not a priest

1105
02:09:01,694 --> 02:09:03,810
You may fill in the notification.
A month afterwards. . .

1106
02:09:03,894 --> 02:09:06,169
you may come to get married.
- But. . .

1107
02:09:23,054 --> 02:09:27,047
Your sister left a while ago.
She wasn't in a good shape

1108
02:09:27,134 --> 02:09:29,728
What happened to her?
- She read your letter

1109
02:09:29,814 --> 02:09:34,968
Then she went insane! Didn't even
recognise me. She's in bad shape

1110
02:09:37,534 --> 02:09:42,562
Oh, what am I to do?

1111
02:09:47,134 --> 02:09:50,809
The family always
interferes till the wedding is over

1112
02:09:51,174 --> 02:09:53,404
In a while, the two
of you will patch up

1113
02:09:59,454 --> 02:10:04,369
Didi is in a bad shape.
She's so miserable. . .

1114
02:10:05,574 --> 02:10:08,929
Where is she?
- I don't know

1115
02:10:09,014 --> 02:10:11,812
She seems to have left here in
a disturbed state a while ago

1116
02:10:22,694 --> 02:10:26,972
Didn't you have this shoulder
to weep on? Why that shoulder?

1117
02:10:31,574 --> 02:10:35,169
Mr Verma, this is Gupta. I'm
calling from your residence

1118
02:10:35,254 --> 02:10:37,290
Has Ms Amita reached home?

1119
02:10:37,654 --> 02:10:39,963
She seems to have left a
while ago in a disturbed state.

1120
02:10:40,054 --> 02:10:42,204
Where might she have gone?

1121
02:10:42,454 --> 02:10:45,844
There's a board
meeting today. Maybe. . .

1122
02:10:54,814 --> 02:10:57,282
We've waited long enough.
Maybe Ms Amita and Mr Verma. . .

1123
02:10:57,374 --> 02:11:00,844
don't wish to attend this meeting.
- Let them not

1124
02:11:01,774 --> 02:11:04,334
Gentlemen, the quorum is full

1125
02:11:04,854 --> 02:11:08,847
I request Mr
Gulabchand to chair the meeting

1126
02:11:15,414 --> 02:11:18,451
Some members wish to move
a no-confidence motion. . .

1127
02:11:18,534 --> 02:11:20,603
against the managing director.

1128
02:11:20,974 --> 02:11:22,692
We have to decide. . .

1129
02:11:22,774 --> 02:11:28,087
whether Ms Amita
remains our managing director

1130
02:11:29,134 --> 02:11:32,604
Welcome Mr Verma. We
have been expecting you

1131
02:11:44,894 --> 02:11:46,566
No!

1132
02:11:48,174 --> 02:11:49,926
Don't look at me like that!

1133
02:11:51,094 --> 02:11:54,166
Don't look at me in anger! No!

1134
02:11:56,174 --> 02:11:58,642
I know why you're angry

1135
02:12:01,774 --> 02:12:06,325
For my sake, Babli
has ruined her life!

1136
02:12:09,214 --> 02:12:11,284
Not here.
- Where might she be?

1137
02:12:11,374 --> 02:12:13,603
At home perhaps?
- Let's look in the library

1138
02:12:13,774 --> 02:12:16,766
I think. . .

1139
02:12:21,574 --> 02:12:23,690
I swear by you !

1140
02:12:23,774 --> 02:12:30,691
For the sake of your Babli,
I can even give my life!

1141
02:12:32,654 --> 02:12:38,411
Just think. The newspaper we've
pumped millions into, is our enemy

1142
02:12:38,494 --> 02:12:41,486
I went along with them
for the sake of the paper!

1143
02:12:43,494 --> 02:12:46,769
The ones I trusted
turn out to be my enemies!

1144
02:12:47,854 --> 02:12:54,885
They want to throw me out! They
want to grab my father's newspaper

1145
02:12:56,054 --> 02:12:58,932
Didi. . .
- Open up

1146
02:13:00,614 --> 02:13:03,286
I won't let them have
my father's newspaper!

1147
02:13:03,934 --> 02:13:08,291
You hear? I shall never let that be!

1148
02:13:08,734 --> 02:13:11,612
Never! Never!

1149
02:13:43,214 --> 02:13:44,966
Call a doctor

1150
02:13:51,574 --> 02:13:56,647
No Mr Verma ! Not as long as I'm alive!

1151
02:13:57,734 --> 02:13:59,690
Never!
- What. . . ?

1152
02:14:04,974 --> 02:14:07,408
After I'm gone. . .

1153
02:14:11,694 --> 02:14:16,722
Mr Verma, call Jitendra

1154
02:14:19,054 --> 02:14:23,252
Jiten is right here, Didi
Why can't she recognise people?

1155
02:14:23,734 --> 02:14:25,531
You want to tell Jitendra something?

1156
02:14:26,934 --> 02:14:33,533
Tell him I haven't
mortgaged Daddy's old office

1157
02:14:35,454 --> 02:14:39,447
Let him start a new paper from here.
- I shall tell him that

1158
02:14:39,774 --> 02:14:44,894
But don't ever tell him that. . .
- What. . . ?

1159
02:14:48,654 --> 02:14:50,406
That I too. . .

1160
02:14:52,094 --> 02:14:54,733
Never tell him that! Never!

1161
02:14:56,574 --> 02:15:03,206
Just tell him to start a new paper

1162
02:15:07,054 --> 02:15:13,527
The Eternal Spring will return

